    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>When I checking <a href="http://angularjs.org/">Angular</a>, notice a new live demo named <em>Javascript Projects</em> which using <strong>angularFire.js</strong>.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.firebase.com/">Firebase</a> is a scalable real-time backend, give you the ability to build apps fast without managing servers. A real-time chat app in 14 lines of code. Like:</p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
<span class='line-number'>9</span>
<span class='line-number'>10</span>
<span class='line-number'>11</span>
<span class='line-number'>12</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>var messagesRef = new Firebase(&lsquo;&lt;a href="https://chat.firebaseIO.com/">https://chat.firebaseIO.com/&lt;/a>&rsquo;);&lt;/p>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p>// write messages
</span><span class='line'>messagesRef.push({name:&lsquo;Jenux&rsquo;, text:&lsquo;Firebase is awesome!&rsquo;})&lt;/p>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p>// Read messages
</span><span class='line'>messageRef.on(&lsquo;child_added&rsquo;, function(message) {&lt;/p>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;pre>&lt;code>renderMessage(message.val());
</span><span class='line'>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>
</span><span class='line'>
</span><span class='line'>&lt;p>});</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p>on March 29, 2013, <strong>Angular</strong> realeased <a href="http://github.com/firebase/angularFire">AngularFire</a> to support Firebase binding. I&rsquo;m trying to implement the <a href="http://firebase.github.com/angularFire/examples/todomvc/">live demo</a> mentioned in the news to get better understanding about <strong>AngularFire</strong>.</p>

<p>For practise, I want:</p>

<ul>
<li>Using <a href="/blog/2013/07/02/bower-package-manager-for-web-by-twitter/">bower</a> to manager source libs</li>
<li>Using <a href="https://www.firebase.com/">fireBase</a> as the data source</li>
</ul>


<p>Fowlloing is the log how I work on this for you to reference, and welcome to leave your suggestion help me to improve it.</p>

<!-- more -->


